Parliament, Thursday, 2 March 2023 – The Portfolio Committee on Transport will this Saturday, 4 March 2023, conduct public hearings on the Railway Safety Bill [B7-2021] in the Northern Cape at Moses Links Community Hall in Upington between 10 am and 2 pm.
	
	On Sunday, the committee will proceed with public hearings at De Aar Town Hall in De Aar between 10 am and 2 pm.
	
	The people of ZF Mgcawu and Pixley ka Seme districts in Northern Cape will have an opportunity to comment on the Bill, which seeks to improve the regulatory framework regulating railway safety in South Africa in order to improve the safety of passengers and freight.
	
	The Bill furthermore seeks to provide guidance on the governance of the Railway Safety Regulator (RSR) and to address operators’ concerns raised over time about South Africa’s system of railway safety. It places the emphasis and focus on railway safety, and recognises operators’ role in managing and implementing safety measures, with the RSR promoting safety and ensuring compliance with such measures.
	
	The public hearings are conducted in terms of Section 59 (1) (a) of the Constitution of the Republic of South Africa, which requires the National Assembly (NA) to facilitate public involvement in the legislative and other processes of the NA and its committees. Members of the media are invited to attend these public hearings.
	
	ISSUED BY THE PARLIAMENTARY COMMUNICATION SERVICES.
	
